"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-daniel-wiffen-paris-2024-olympics-hospital-river-seine-b2594942.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Wiffen won 800m freestyle gold in the pool before competing in the open water swim in the River Seine  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Irish swimmer Daniel Wiffen was \\\"rushed to hospital\\\" after being forced to pull out of the closing ceremony due to illness having been in line to carry his nation's flag.\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 449, \"end\": 454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.8981206643112671, \"rank\": 0.11225933010149021, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffensecured gold in the 800 metres freestyleat La Defense Arena, making history as thefirst Irish man to win an Olympic goldin the pool.\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 715, \"end\": 720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.8981206643112671, \"rank\": 0.11225933010149021, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He subsquentlyadded a bronze medalin the 1,500m freestyle, before entering and completing the first open water event of his career, eventually finishing 18th after agruelling 10km swim through the River Seine.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 958, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Wiffen has now revealed that he became \\\"very unwell\\\" ahead of the closing ceremony having been chosen as one of Ireland's flagbearers at the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.8480146913095343, \"rank\": 0.14017202315449176, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thanks everyone who reached out, I am incredibly disappointed to miss out on the opportunity to be flag bearer last night,\\\" Wiffensaid on social media.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yesterday I rushed to hospital as I was very unwell with a bug that I am being treated for, and am feeling better now.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope everyone enjoys the evening and I hope to be well enough to seeing everyone when we get home.\\\"\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His illness may bring fresh scrutiny onthe water quality of the Seineafter a series of postponements and cancellations oftraining events in the riverduring the course ofParis 2024.\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medal-winning rower Fintan McCarthy stepped in alongside breaststroke bronze medallist Mona McSharry for Ireland at the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1719, \"end\": 1734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fintan McCarthy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\"}, {\"begin\": 1786, \"end\": 1799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mona McSharry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.8480146913095343, \"rank\": 0.14017202315449176, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McSharry and Wiffen became Ireland's second and third Olympicswimmingmedallists as the nation secured seven podium finishes in Paris, a new high.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.8480146913095343, \"rank\": 0.14017202315449176, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1965, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999921926701, \"rank\": 7.807439314063263e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 23-year-old freestyler Wiffen was born in Leeds but raised in Magheralin, though is now based at Loughborough University.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2031, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\", \"score\": 0.9937235738179857, \"rank\": 0.0037292602153003486, \"text\": \"Leeds\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leeds\"}, {\"begin\": 2051, \"end\": 2061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magheralin\", \"score\": 0.9999999999856755, \"rank\": 9.546022916955527e-12, \"text\": \"Magheralin\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magheralin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magheralin\"}, {\"begin\": 2086, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loughborough_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1972307906731648e-14, \"text\": \"Loughborough University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loughborough_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Loughborough_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two-time world champion said that theOlympicsmarked his \\\"first and last\\\" competitive open water swim shortly after exiting the Seine.\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999915085027, \"rank\": 7.257867743858692e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the pool it is easy when there are eight people in a final, and there are about 30 people in it here,\\\" Wiffen explained.\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was about two minutes down from the front of the pack.\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was like 'do I really want to finish?\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"', but I needed to finish it and I am glad to say I am an Olympic open-water swimmer.\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A lot of people would say it's the worst race they have ever done, in terms of the currents.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So for my first one to be the hardest and I came 18th, I am very happy.\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am Olympic champion, Olympic bronze medallist and placed 18th in the open water.\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I could not have asked for anything more.\\\"\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 3086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2907, \"end\": 2918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999903925527, \"rank\": 9.57355949831062e-09, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"